                                <date>1958</date>. С. <biblScope unit="page">??–??</biblScope>.</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><encodingDesc><tagsDecl>&amp;renditions;</tagsDecl></encodingDesc></teiHeader><text><body><entry xml:id="entry_kʼaba" xml:lang="os"><form type="lemma"><orth>kʼaba</orth></form><sense><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>платье женское</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>women dress</q></tr></sense><re><form type="lemma"><orth>kʼabajag</orth></form><sense><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>материал на платье</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>material for the dress</q></tr></sense></re><exampleGrp><example><quote>moj yn k˳y wa, wæd yn kʼabatæj fyldær cy lxænʒæn</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>когда у нее будет муж, он ей будет покупать много платьев</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>when she has a husband, he will buy her many dresses</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Arsen"/><biblScope>37</biblScope></bibl></example><example><quote>Fatʼi ralasta kæcæjdær kʼabajag</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>Фати вытащила откуда-то материал на платье</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>Fati pulled out material on the dress from somewhere</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Arsen"/><biblScope>37</biblScope></bibl></example><example><quote>Marine jæ kʼabajy fæḱḱījæ jæ cæsty sygtæ asærfta</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>Марине вытерла слезы подолом платья</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>Marine wiped her tears with the hem of her dress</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Сека"/><biblScope>95</biblScope></bibl></example></exampleGrp><exampleGrp><example><quote>moj yn k˳y wa, wæd yn kʼabatæj fyldær cy lxænʒæn</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>когда у нее будет муж, он ей будет покупать много платьев</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>when she has a husband, he will buy her many dresses</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Arsen"/><biblScope>37</biblScope></bibl></example><example><quote>Fatʼi ralasta kæcæjdær kʼabajag</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>Фати вытащила откуда-то материал на платье</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>Fati pulled out material on the dress from somewhere</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Arsen"/><biblScope>37</biblScope></bibl></example><example><quote>Marine jæ kʼabajy fæḱḱījæ jæ cæsty sygtæ asærfta</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>Марине вытерла слезы подолом платья</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>Marine wiped her tears with the hem of her dress</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Сека"/><biblScope>95</biblScope></bibl></example></exampleGrp><etym xml:lang="ru">Из <mentioned xml:lang=""><lang/> <w>qabā</w> <gloss><q>верхнее платье</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang=""><w/> <gloss><q>плащ</q></gloss></mentioned>, . Вероятно, через грузинское посредство: <mentioned xml:lang="ka"><lang/> <w>k’ābā</w> <gloss><q>кафтан</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="ka"><w/> <gloss><q>платье</q></gloss></mentioned>, . Вошло во многие языки Кавказа: <mentioned xml:lang="ab"><lang/> <w>a-k’aba</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sva"><lang/> <w>k’ab</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ce"><lang/> <w>ghabali</w></mentioned> и др. Сюда же <mentioned xml:lang="trk"><lang/> <w>qaba</w></mentioned> (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Радлов"/><biblScope>II 434</biblScope></bibl>). Первоисточник всей группы — иранский; ср. <mentioned xml:lang="pal"><lang/> <w>kapāh</w> <gloss><q>плащ</q></gloss></mentioned>. %sВailеу%s привлекает также <mentioned xml:lang="sa-vaidika"><lang/> <w>kapa-</w> <gloss><q>сбруя</q></gloss></mentioned> (?) и возводит к и.е. %i*kap-%i ‘обхватывать’ и пр. Славянская группа слов — <mentioned xml:lang="ru"><lang/> <w>кабат</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang=""><lang/> <w>kabat</w></mentioned> и пр.— восходит к тому же источнику, но через греческое посредство (<mentioned xml:lang="grc"><lang/> <w>καβάδης</w></mentioned> (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Berneker"/><biblScope>464</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Lokotsch"/><biblScope>77</biblScope></bibl>).%n<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>53, 87, 519</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><author>Bailey</author><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_TPhS"/><biblScope xml:lang="ru">1954, стр. 146—153</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">1954, p. 146—153</biblScope></bibl>.</etym><etym xml:lang="en">From <mentioned xml:lang=""><lang/> <w>qabā</w> <gloss><q>coat</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang=""><w/> <gloss><q>raincoat</q></gloss></mentioned>, . Probably, through the Georgian agency: <mentioned xml:lang="ka"><lang/> <w>k’ābā</w> <gloss><q>caftan</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="ka"><w/> <gloss><q>dress</q></gloss></mentioned>, . It entered many Caucasian languages: <mentioned xml:lang="ab"><lang/> <w>a-k’aba</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sva"><lang/> <w>k’ab</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ce"><lang/> <w>ghabali</w></mentioned> etc. <mentioned xml:lang="trk"><lang/> <w>qaba</w></mentioned> is related to it as well (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Радлов"/><biblScope>II 434</biblScope></bibl>). The primary source of all group is Iranian; cf. <mentioned xml:lang="pal"><lang/> <w>kapāh</w> <gloss><q>raincoat</q></gloss></mentioned>. %sВailеу%s attracts also <mentioned xml:lang="sa-vaidika"><lang/> <w>kapa-</w> <gloss><q>harness</q></gloss></mentioned> (?) and traces it back to Indo-European %i*kap-%i ‘embrace’ etc. Slavic word group — <mentioned xml:lang="ru"><lang/> <w>кабат</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang=""><lang/> <w>kabat</w></mentioned> etc. — traces to the same source, but through the Greek agency (<mentioned xml:lang="grc"><lang/> <w>καβάδης</w></mentioned> (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Berneker"/><biblScope>464</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Lokotsch"/><biblScope>77</biblScope></bibl>).%n<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>53, 87, 519</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><author>Bailey</author><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_TPhS"/><biblScope xml:lang="ru">1954, стр. 146—153</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">1954, p. 146—153</biblScope></bibl>.</etym></entry></body></text></TEI>